OL,6,FThe HSE determined that the company's
OL,7,Frisk assessment was not suitable as it
OL,8,Freferenced control measures that were
OL,9,Fnot present at the market.JJ.J. Morris
OL,10,FLimited, of Haverfordwest, pleaded
OL,11,Fguilty to breaching the Health and
OL,12,FSafety at Work Act 1974.
OL,14,FThe company was fined #75,000 and
OL,15,Fordered to pay #5,047.55 in costs at
OL,16,FLlanelli Magistrates' Court on
OL,17,FTuesday, June 20.
